# GEE Scripts

Google Earth Engine (GEE) JavaScript scripts for the spatial
data extraction and model deployment components of this study.

## Scripts

| File | Purpose | Output |
|------|---------|--------|
| `01_S2_GSE_extraction.js` | Extract Sentinel-2 annual percentile composites and GSE embedding values at field survey locations; export as CSV for use in R scripts | CSV files (input for STEP_01 to STEP_05 R scripts) |
| `02_SPC_spatial_deployment.js` | Train two-stage RF model (Stage A: morphology classification; Stage B: SPC regression) and deploy spatially per survey year | SPC prediction rasters per year in GEE Assets and Google Drive |
| `03_GEE_app_viewer.js` | Interactive web application for visual exploration of SPC predictions across study sites | Live app: https://muhammadhafizt.users.earthengine.app/view/seagrasspercentcoverindonesia |

---

## Workflow

Run scripts in the following order:

```
01_S2_GSE_extraction.js
      |
      v
  CSV files exported to Google Drive
      |
      v
  R scripts (STEP_01 to STEP_05)
      |
      v
02_SPC_spatial_deployment.js
      |
      v
  SPC rasters exported to GEE Assets
      |
      v
03_GEE_app_viewer.js  (loads rasters from GEE Assets)
```

---

## Requirements

- A Google Earth Engine account: https://earthengine.google.com
- Access to the GEE Code Editor: https://code.earthengine.google.com
- Field survey training data (see Data Availability Statement in paper)

